summary: People in the fandom might have come across this list: 01. Emperor (Satan/Lucifer) 02. Great Kings 03. Kings 04. Great Princes...
body:
People in the fandom might have come across this list:

  • 01. Emperor (Satan/Lucifer)
  • 02. Great Kings
  • 03. Kings
  • 04. Great Princes
  • 05. Princes
  • 06. Great Marquises
  • 07. Marquises
  • 08. Great Dukes
  • 09. Dukes
  • 10. Great Earls
  • 11. Earls
  • 12. Great Presidents
  • 12. Presidents
  • 13. Knights
  • 14. Great Marshals

That’s the (apparently most commonly used) Hierarchy of Hell.

The last entry says ‘Great Marshals’, which would mean below it there’d be ‘Marshal’. Below that, taking into account that the book these ranks come from (Ars Goetia/Lesser Keys of Solomon) is a work from England, it’s easily possible that the rank below this might be Sheriff and the rank below that, in turn, might, indeed, be 'Local Councillor’.

This would mean that, even if Crowley isn’t 'even a local councillor’ he might not be as low in rank as it might appear.

summary: My personal nightmare is Good Omens series ending with Aziraphale and Crowley being turned into humans by their superiors as a...
body: My personal nightmare is Good Omens series ending with Aziraphale and Crowley being turned into humans by their superiors as a punishment for their rebellion. I’ve discussed this scenario many times with my fandom friends, I’ve read, written and translated a lot of fanfiction with similar plot twists, but it has always felt bittersweet because I’ve done all this knowing that everything is all right in the book. But if this turns out to be canon, I’ll literally cry. This is terrifying, even if they get to spend the rest of their lives together in their lovely South Downs cottage or elsewhere. The thought of them dying is excruciating. Please, Mr. Gaiman, don’t make this happen!
